---
title: "Join Us - Developer - Join our team as a developer"

header:
  title: "join us"
  subtitle: "ruby on rails developer"

introduction:
  title: "Are you a Ruby on Rails developer?"
  text_1: "We are looking for Ruby on Rails developers to join our London office."
  text_2: "Recognised as being key members in the community, our developers are responsible for building scalable, sustainable systems from project inception right through to production."
  text_3: "We need people who can:"
  requirements:
    - Develop and maintain complex Ruby on Rails applications through agile ways of working
    - Make informed decisions quickly drawing from experience across a wide technical stack
    - Involve your team in discussions on progress of stories
    - Turn designs and wireframes into functional applications

developers_image:
  image: "/jobs/images/developers-1.jpg"
  image_description: "Developers presenting code"

description:
  title: "Key competencies and skills"
  requirements:
    - Solid experience in Ruby and Ruby on Rails
    - Experience of version control (ideally Git)
    - TDD/BDD experience
    - SQL (preferably MySQL or PostgreSQL)
    - Architect, develop and maintain complex Ruby and Rails applications
    - Ability to work with other developers and QA testers to plan and ship projects
    - Able to identify areas of risk and complexity during the planning process
    - Communicate continually with team on progress of stories
    - Can turn wireframes and designs into functional applications
    - Write and maintain integration and unit test suites

other_requirements:
  title: "Highly desirable"
  requirements:
    - HTML and CSS experience
    - Experience working in an agile environment
    - Open source contributions
    - Experience setting up and maintaining UNIX systems
    - JavaScript
    - A keen eye for detail
    - Understanding of continuous integration and delivery
  image: "/jobs/images/developers-2.jpg"
  image_description: "Developer at work"

benefits:
  title: "Benefits of working with us"
  list:
    - 25 holiday days per year, on top of the bank holiday allowance
    - Holiday flexibility and loyalty bonus benefits
    - An informal, startup culture of growth and flexible working hours
    - 10 Innovation Days per year
    - A generous conference budget to attend the conferences of your choice
    - A peer-to-peer mentoring programme
    - Life assurance policy at 4x salary
    - A workplace pension with Standard Life
    - A 'Bike To Work' scheme

developers_meeting_image:
  image: "/jobs/images/developers-3.jpg"
  image_description: "Developers meetup"

other_benefits:
  title: "Other benefits include"
  list:
    - Weekly reflection and drinks at our Whines & Cheers session (our Friday evening company retrospective)
    - Bi-annual reviews
    - The potential for equity in an Unboxed 'spin-off' product
    - Monthly 'Linkers & Thinkers' lunches
    - Your own caricature

process:
  title: "What next?"
  text_1: "Send us your CV and, if we think you will make a good team member, we will get you to complete a short coding exercise. This gives you the an opportunity to showcase your approach to solving problems and for us to see your code on a clean build project."
  text_2: "If we like what we see we will invite you in for a pairing session with one of our developers where we will talk over the choices you have made in your solution and get to know you a little better."
  image: "/jobs/images/developers-4.jpg"
  image_description: "Developers working together"

developer_quote:
  quote: "My goal is to become the best developer I can be and, for me, this ultimately means being part of a productive and stimulating community that cares about adopting best practices and sharing knowledge. That’s why I joined the Unboxed team. I believe these concepts are at the core of our success in producing high quality web applications."
  source: "Neil van Beinum, Ruby on Rails Developer"
  image: "/assets/images/people/neil-van-beinum.png"

contact_us:
  title: "Send us your CV"
  text_1: "Claire is our “people gardener” and she would love to hear from you."
  text_2: "We like to do the most valuable things first - employing you could be exactly that."
  text_3: "Send your CV through to Claire at: "
  email: "iwantajob@unboxed.co"
  text_4: "From there, she'll be in touch. Good luck!"
  image: "/jobs/images/ubxd-gardener2.jpg"
  image_description: "Our gardener at work"

related:
  title: "Related"
  articles:
